You can now use the [latest release `maven-shade-plugin:3.2.0` as of 13.09.2018](https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ReleaseNote.jspa?projectId=12317921&amp;version=12343491) which shall solve the error while using `minimizeJar` (with JDK8+) :

    &lt;plugin&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-shade-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
      &lt;version&gt;3.2.0&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;

Please take a look at this tutorial from Maven: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-shade-plugin/usage.html

The configuration of the plugin changed a bit over past and you don&#39;t need to specify the transformations.

An example looks like this for 3.2.1:
```
&lt;project&gt;
  ...
  &lt;build&gt;
    &lt;plugins&gt;
      &lt;plugin&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-shade-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;3.2.1&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;configuration&gt;
          &lt;!-- put your configurations here --&gt;
        &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;executions&gt;
          &lt;execution&gt;
            &lt;phase&gt;package&lt;/phase&gt;
            &lt;goals&gt;
              &lt;goal&gt;shade&lt;/goal&gt;
            &lt;/goals&gt;
          &lt;/execution&gt;
        &lt;/executions&gt;
      &lt;/plugin&gt;
    &lt;/plugins&gt;
  &lt;/build&gt;
  ...
&lt;/project&gt;
```

